{
  "name": "swift-checkout",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node swift-checkout-server.js"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "*",
    "multer": "*",
    "nodemailer": "*",
    "cors": "*"
  }
}
```

The `"*"` means "install whatever version is available" — removes any version mismatch issues.

**Also check these two things in GitHub:**

1. Is the file named exactly `swift-checkout-server.js`? (no capital letters, no spaces)
2. Are both files in the **root** of the repo — not inside a folder?

It should look like this in your GitHub repo:
```
swift-checkout/
├── swift-checkout-server.js
└── package.json
